  <brief_title>Safety and Efficacy of RC-1291 HCl in Patients With Cancer Related Anorexia and Weight Loss</brief_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>Helsinn Therapeutics (U.S.), Inc</agency>
      <agency_class>Industry</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Helsinn Therapeutics (U.S.), Inc</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Anorexia and weight loss are devastating complications in late-stage cancer patients and is
      strongly associated with mortality in these patients. Activation of Ghrelin receptors have
      been demonstrated to stimulate appetite. RC-1291 HCl, by virtue of its ghrelin like activity
      and Growth Hormone releasing effects may have a dual role in the reversal of cancer induced
      anorexia and weight loss. This study will test the safety and efficacy of RC-1291 in the
      treatment of cancer patients with anorexia and weight loss.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
